  "prompt": "What does \"followed by None\" mean in Instagram search?",
  "response": "When you see \"followed by None\" in an Instagram search, it typically means that the user you are searching for is not following anyone on the platform. \n\nHere's a breakdown of what this could imply:\n\n1. **Private Account**: The user may have a private account and has chosen not to follow anyone, or they may have recently unfollowed all accounts they were previously following.\n\n2. **New Account**: The user might have just created their account and hasn't followed anyone yet.\n\n3. **Curated Following List**: The user may have intentionally chosen not to follow anyone as part of their social media strategy or personal preference.\n\n4. **Account Cleanup**: The user might have gone through a period of cleaning up their following list and has unfollowed everyone.\n\nIn essence, \"followed by None\" is simply an indication that the user is not currently following any other Instagram accounts.",
